Implemented `T1.2` directly in-repo with superpowers-style test-first flow, without any waveplan write actions.

**Concrete Changes**
- Added explicit review sidecar path resolution contract in CLI:
  - precedence: `--review-schedule` then `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW`
  - fail-fast when missing
  - fail-fast when sidecar path equals `--schedule`
  - [waveplan-cli](/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/waveplan-cli#L350)
- Added `--review-schedule` flag to SWIM subcommands:
  - `next`, `step`, `run`, `journal`
  - [waveplan-cli](/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/waveplan-cli#L763)
- Wired resolution checks into execution paths for those subcommands:
  - [waveplan-cli](/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/waveplan-cli#L892)
- Extended CLI scaffold test coverage for:
  - help surface includes `--review-schedule`
  - deterministic collision error (`review schedule must differ from --schedule`)
  - [test_t4_1_cli_scaffold.sh](/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/tests/swim/test_t4_1_cli_scaffold.sh#L26)
- Updated SWIM wired integration test setup for new contract + sandbox stability env:
  - sets `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW`, `GOCACHE`, `WAVEPLAN_SWIM_ARTIFACT_ROOT`
  - [test_t4_2_cli_wired.sh](/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/tests/swim/test_t4_2_cli_wired.sh#L9)
- Updated installed-anydir test to provide `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW`:
  - [test_installed_anydir.sh](/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/tests/swim/test_installed_anydir.sh#L30)

**Verification Commands + Results**
